The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: The Raju familys holding in Satyam Computer Services has dropped by over three per cent after a share sale by lenders. In a filing with the Bombay Stock Exchange, the company said SRSR Holdings stake in Satyam had come down to 5.13 per cent because of the sale of shares pledged by the promoters to lenders to raise funds. Rajus family had held 8.27 per cent through SRSR Holdings at the end of the September quarter.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: Suzlon Energy will sell a 10 per cent stake in its Belgium arm Hansen to a London-based investment firm for an undisclosed amount. The companys Netherlands-based wholly owned subsidiary AE-Rotor Holding has sold 6.70 crore shares in Hansen to Ecofin.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: Kingfisher will cut fares by 21-65 per cent. The revised fares will be effective from January 1, Kingfisher Airlines chairman and CEO Vijay Mallya said.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: Sebi has lodged an FIR with the Mumbai police for forgery of its communication in the wake of the Pyramid Saimira theatre episode.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 2: Transporters have called an indefinite nationwide strike from January 5 to press for their demands, including reduction in diesel prices.                                                                                                                                
